Mary Day claimed £16,500 of income support and disability allowance despite having £27,000 in savings in the bank . 
  She used taxpayers' money to go on luxury holidays to the Indian resort of Goa . 
  Day went on three trips to Goa in 2009, 2011 and 2014 but did not tell the authorities . 
  She was sentenced to three months in prison but suspended for 12 months . 
 